    <description>Control Room is a Windows desktop application for local-first script execution and task management. It provides evidence-grade observability, failure fingerprinting, and a command palette for managing automation workflows.

## Features

- Local-first SQLite storage (works offline, no server required)
- Evidence-grade run tracking with full reproducibility metadata
- Failure fingerprinting and recurring failure detection
- Command palette with fuzzy search
- Profile-based script execution with environment overrides
- ZIP export of run evidence
- Timeline filtering by failure fingerprint

## Notes

- Requires Windows 10 version 1809 (build 17763) or later
- Self-contained deployment (no .NET runtime installation required)
- Installs to Chocolatey tools directory
